After five years, the guilty man
confessed. I was released.

164
00:14:15,733 --> 00:14:18,691
But I lost everything.
The lawyers took my fortune...

165
00:14:18,893 --> 00:14:20,690
...my wife divorced me...

166
00:14:20,853 --> 00:14:23,686
...my home was broken up.
Everything.

167
00:14:23,893 --> 00:14:26,532
Those two bloodhounds
ruined my life.

168
00:14:26,693 --> 00:14:29,332
I had to flee to Mexico
to start life anew.

169
00:14:29,493 --> 00:14:31,927
But someday, I'll run across
them again...

170
00:14:32,133 --> 00:14:33,885
...and when I do...

171
00:14:34,093 --> 00:14:37,290
...I'm going to skin them alive.
- Uh-huh.

172
00:14:37,453 --> 00:14:39,045
First, the little one...

173
00:14:39,253 --> 00:14:40,606
...then the big one.

174
00:14:40,813 --> 00:14:45,409
- I'm going to skin them alive.
- Take it easy, Richard K.

175
00:14:46,573 --> 00:14:48,848
[WOMEN CHATTER INDISTINCTLY]

176
00:14:57,773 --> 00:15:01,049
Oh, there is the great Don Sebastian.

177
00:15:01,253 --> 00:15:03,369
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

178
00:15:07,373 --> 00:15:11,332
Don't sit there, our other clothes
are not dry yet.

179
00:15:13,133 --> 00:15:16,011
My hero.

180
00:15:34,653 --> 00:15:37,292
Come on, snap out of it.

181
00:15:41,333 --> 00:15:43,210
Wipe your mouth.

182
