204
00:16:49,613 --> 00:16:52,730
I beg your pardon, sir,
but why do you ask?

205
00:16:52,933 --> 00:16:54,366
Well, I'm in business with him.

206
00:16:54,533 --> 00:16:57,570
- I left his office not over an hour ago.
- An hour ago?

207
00:16:57,773 --> 00:16:59,923
Well, how did he get out
of prison so soon?

208
00:17:00,133 --> 00:17:03,409
After five years, they found he
was innocent. The real guy confessed.

209
00:17:03,773 --> 00:17:05,365
- Innocent?
- That's right.

210
00:17:05,573 --> 00:17:07,245
Gee, that's terrible.

211
00:17:07,493 --> 00:17:10,326
Maybe you better go apologize.
That's an awful thing to do to.

212
00:17:10,533 --> 00:17:12,251
I better go and apologize?

213
00:17:12,413 --> 00:17:15,211
Why, you were the one
that so falsely accused him.

214
00:17:15,373 --> 00:17:18,410
Why, if you had a spark of manhood
left in your system...

215
00:17:18,613 --> 00:17:21,173
...you'd go right over
and apologize to Mr. Muldoon.

216
00:17:21,373 --> 00:17:22,886
- I'll do that...
- Just a minute.

217
00:17:23,093 --> 00:17:25,368
If you'll take my tip
you'll never cross his path...

218
00:17:25,573 --> 00:17:28,371
...because he said he was
gonna skin you both alive.

219
00:17:28,573 --> 00:17:30,689
Now, if you're smart
you'll get out of town...

220
00:17:30,893 --> 00:17:33,771
...because he said, "First
the little one then the big one...

221
00:17:33,973 --> 00:17:36,567
...I'll skin them both alive."

222
00:17:36,813 --> 00:17:39,646
- Thanks for the information.
- Good day, gentlemen.

223
00:17:39,853 --> 00:17:41,969
- Good day.
- Goodbye.

224
00:17:48,093 --> 00:17:49,845
Sit down.

225
00:17:51,493 --> 00:17:53,882
Over here.

226
00:17:55,093 --> 00:17:59,052
Well, here's another nice mess
you've gotten me into.

227
00:17:59,733 --> 00:18:01,371
- You know what?
- What?

228
00:18:01,573 --> 00:18:05,327
We'd better find Larceny Nell and get
back to Peoria as fast as we can.

229
00:18:05,533 --> 00:18:09,651
I guess you're right. We certainly
don't want to be skinned alive.

230
00:18:09,853 --> 00:18:14,210
I should say not. I don't want to walk
around in my bones...

231
00:18:14,413 --> 00:18:16,131
...rattling all over the place.

232
00:18:21,413 --> 00:18:25,452
I didn't think it was possible there was
another face like that in all the world.

233
00:18:44,213 --> 00:18:48,172
- I wish you good luck, señor.
- Thank you. We need it.

234
00:18:55,333 --> 00:18:58,006
