Psst! She's at the cocktail bar.

239
00:19:11,653 --> 00:19:14,008
Atlantic City.

240
00:19:19,213 --> 00:19:20,612
- Come on.
- Where are you going?

241
00:19:20,813 --> 00:19:23,168
- I've found Larceny Nell.
- Where is she?

242
00:19:23,373 --> 00:19:26,604
She shook hands a moment ago,
and you didn't even recognize her.

243
00:19:26,813 --> 00:19:28,405
Come on.

244
00:19:47,453 --> 00:19:49,444
Won't you join me in a drink,
Don Sebastian?

245
00:19:49,653 --> 00:19:51,211
Madam, he's not a bullfighter.

246
00:19:51,373 --> 00:19:54,763
We're detectives
and you're under arrest.

247
00:19:56,293 --> 00:19:59,365
You can't arrest me. I'm on Mexican
territory. You can't touch me.

248
00:19:59,533 --> 00:20:01,649
We can't, huh?
We have the papers.

249
00:20:01,813 --> 00:20:04,566
- What papers?
- The extradition papers.

250
00:20:04,733 --> 00:20:07,645
- Are you kidding?
- Kidding?

251
00:20:13,413 --> 00:20:16,325
- So, what?
- You give me back those papers.

252
00:20:16,533 --> 00:20:18,569
- Try and get them.
- I certainly...

253
00:20:18,773 --> 00:20:21,651
Papers or no papers, you're coming
with us. Get the handcuffs.

254
00:20:21,813 --> 00:20:24,566
- Get the handcuffs, Stanley.
- Get your hands off of me.

255
00:20:24,733 --> 00:20:26,325
Take your hands off of me.

256
00:20:26,493 --> 00:20:28,643
- Get the handcuffs, quick.
- Let me go.

257
00:20:28,853 --> 00:20:30,571
I'll not.

258
00:20:34,853 --> 00:20:36,127
Come on, Stanley, help me.

259
00:20:36,293 --> 00:20:38,204
- Here.
- Let me go.

260
00:20:39,533 --> 00:20:43,765
Madam, you might as well
come along quietly.

261
00:20:44,013 --> 00:20:45,526
Ooo!

262
00:20:47,213 --> 00:20:50,091
No, no, Stanley.
You can't hit a lady.

263
00:20:50,293 --> 00:20:52,329
She's no lady.

264
00:20:52,533 --> 00:20:54,683
I'm not, huh?

265
00:21:44,093 --> 00:21:45,970
[LAUGHS]

266
00:22:55,253 --> 00:22:57,369
[LAUGHING]

267
00:23:31,053 --> 00:23:32,850
[EGGS CRUNCH]

268
00:23:53,853 --> 00:23:58,210
Now, you're coming with us or else.

269
00:24:01,013 --> 00:24:02,810
Ooo!

270
00:24:29,533 --> 00:24:32,730
Boss, I got a telegram for you.
It's important.

271
00:24:43,693 --> 00:24:46,332
- How long have you been carrying this?
- About three hours.

272
00:24:46,493 --> 00:24:48,768
We're behind the eight ball,
it ain't transparent.

273
00:24:48,933 --> 00:24:50,730
Don Sebastian's passport's
been held up.

274
00:24:50,893 --> 00:24:54,329
- You mean he ain't coming?
- Not exactly, but I need him here now.

275
00:24:54,533 --> 00:24:56,763
Boss, I got an idea.

276
00:24:57,613 --> 00:24:59,604
- So have I.
- It wasn't my fault.

277
00:24:59,813 --> 00:25:01,166
It wasn't your fault?

278
00:25:01,373 --> 00:25:04,092
I had the dame right in my hand,
and you had to mess it up.

279
00:25:04,293 --> 00:25:06,124
I'm happy to meet you again so soon.

280
00:25:06,333 --> 00:25:08,722
I'm having a difficulty,
and you can do me a favor...

281
00:25:08,933 --> 00:25:10,571
...for which I'm prepared
to pay you.

282
00:25:10,733 --> 00:25:14,248
I'm sorry, but we're not interested.
We have to pack. We're leaving the city.

283
00:25:14,413 --> 00:25:16,973
- Yeah, but this is...
- I'm sorry.

284
00:25:20,173 --> 00:25:22,733
- I wonder what he wanted.
- I don't care what he wanted.

285
00:25:22,893 --> 00:25:24,531
We're gonna pack
and get out of here.

286
00:25:24,733 --> 00:25:27,293
We're going to stay as far away
from that guy as we can.

287
00:25:27,493 --> 00:25:30,849
- Why?
- Because he and Muldoon are like that.

288
00:25:31,053 --> 00:25:32,202
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

289
00:25:32,373 --> 00:25:34,045
Come in.

290
00:25:34,333 --> 00:25:36,289
Pardon me, gentlemen.

291
00:25:36,533 --> 00:25:39,047
- May I use your phone?
- Yeah, help yourself.

292
00:25:39,213 --> 00:25:41,568
Get me Richard K. Muldoon.

293
00:25:44,493 --> 00:25:46,768
Just what was the proposition
you had in the hall?

294
00:25:46,973 --> 00:25:50,648
Remember this morning when I mistook
Mr. Laurel for Don Sebastian?

295
00:25:50,813 --> 00:25:52,485
- Yes.
- By a strange coincidence...

296
00:25:52,653 --> 00:25:55,725
...Mr. Laurel is the living image
of Don Sebastian from Barcelona.

297
00:25:55,933 --> 00:25:59,892
But unfortunately, Don Sebastian
has been held up by passport trouble.

298
00:26:00,093 --> 00:26:01,412
So as a great favor to me...

299
00:26:01,573 --> 00:26:04,565
...and for which, I am prepared
to pay you very handsomely...

300
00:26:04,733 --> 00:26:06,769
...I want you to impersonate him.

301
00:26:06,973 --> 00:26:08,372
I'm not gonna fight any bulls.

302
00:26:08,613 --> 00:26:11,446
- What do you think l...?
- Get me Richard K. Muldoon.

303
00:26:13,333 --> 00:26:15,289
I don't want to fight any bulls.

304
00:26:15,493 --> 00:26:17,484
I don't like bulls.

305
00:26:17,693 --> 00:26:19,570
- I'm allergic to bulls.
- Listen...

306
00:26:19,733 --> 00:26:22,884
...Don Sebastian will certainly
be here for the big bullfight.

307
00:26:23,093 --> 00:26:24,572
I don't have to fight any bulls?

308
00:26:24,773 --> 00:26:28,243
Absolutely not. All I want you to do
is impersonate him, meet the press...

309
00:26:28,413 --> 00:26:31,883
...have your pictures taken, meet all
the ladies, be seen in public places.

310
00:26:32,093 --> 00:26:34,926
I'm taking you out tonight
and show you a good time.

311
00:26:35,653 --> 00:26:38,725
- And we get paid for that?
- Definitely.

312
00:26:41,093 --> 00:26:43,004
But suppose we run across
this Mr. Muldoon?

313
00:26:43,213 --> 00:26:44,771
Oh, leave him to me.

314
00:26:44,973 --> 00:26:46,565
He won't know me
with these clothes?

315
00:26:46,733 --> 00:26:49,964
No. You listen. I'm having my tailor,
Señor Guttenberg, come up here...

316
00:26:50,133 --> 00:26:53,170
...and attire you in the costume
usually worn by bullfighters.

317
00:26:53,453 --> 00:26:54,932
When he gets through with you...

318
00:26:55,093 --> 00:26:57,653
...Mr. Muldoon can look you in the eye
and skin you alive...

319
00:26:57,813 --> 00:27:01,852
I mean, he'll swear you're someone
from Peoria... Barcelona, Spain.

320
00:27:02,053 --> 00:27:04,851
- It's a deal.
- Thank you, sir.

321
00:27:05,053 --> 00:27:06,850
<i>- Adiós. Hasta la vista.</i>
<i>- Adiós.</i>

322
00:27:08,013 --> 00:27:10,573
- Do you think it's all right?
- Of course it's all right.

323
00:27:10,773 --> 00:27:15,051
We'll have a good time
and pick up a few <i>pesos.</i>

324
00:27:18,893 --> 00:27:21,885
[SPANISH MUSIC PLAYS]

325
00:27:49,013 --> 00:27:50,810
- Señor Hotshot.
- Luis.

326
00:27:50,973 --> 00:27:53,851
- And a very distinguished guest.
- You recognize Don Sebastian?

327
00:27:54,013 --> 00:27:57,369
But who could fail? His face
is on every billboard in Mexico City.

328
00:27:57,533 --> 00:27:59,683
- Nice table, Luis.
- The best in the house.

329
00:27:59,893 --> 00:28:02,361
Señorita Tangerine,
Don Sebastian.

330
00:28:02,573 --> 00:28:05,167
Ah, my hero.

331
00:28:13,613 --> 00:28:16,047
That's what I call hospitality.

332
00:28:28,133 --> 00:28:31,603
Remember your dignity.
Steady now.

333
00:28:43,693 --> 00:28:45,126
<i>Sí.</i>

334
00:28:47,893 --> 00:28:51,090
<i>Señores y señoritas,</i>
it is my pleasure to announce...

335
00:28:51,253 --> 00:28:54,404
...that we have with us tonight,
direct from Barcelona...

336
00:28:54,573 --> 00:28:56,803
...the great Don Sebastian.

337
00:28:57,013 --> 00:28:58,685
[CROWD APPLAUDS]

338
00:28:59,013 --> 00:29:01,163
Now, take a bow.

339
00:29:01,333 --> 00:29:04,689
No, get on your feet, take off your hat.
Take a big bow.

340
00:29:15,693 --> 00:29:18,207
- Have you got a match?
- Sure.

341
00:29:18,413 --> 00:29:20,165
No.

342
00:29:21,613 --> 00:29:23,649
Well, light this.

343
00:29:23,853 --> 00:29:25,411
[LAUGHING]

344
00:29:32,173 --> 00:29:34,607
Hey, boss, Muldoon's on his way in.

345
00:29:34,813 --> 00:29:36,565
Muldoon?

346
00:29:37,533 --> 00:29:41,082
Sit down, he won't recognize you,
but don't speak English.

347
00:29:42,733 --> 00:29:45,042
Ah, Hotshot.

348
00:29:46,213 --> 00:29:48,283
- How are you?
- Richard K., meet Don Sebastian.

349
00:29:48,453 --> 00:29:49,727
- How do you do?
<i>- Sí.</i>

350
00:29:49,893 --> 00:29:53,044
- Sit here, you'll see the show better.
- Oh, thanks.

351
00:29:53,573 --> 00:29:57,930
You know, it's a lucky thing for you,
I know you really are Don Sebastian...

352
00:29:58,133 --> 00:30:03,002
...because if you weren't, but the guy
you remind me of, I'd skin you alive.

353
00:30:03,373 --> 00:30:06,809
But then you wouldn't know
what I'm talking about. Ha-ha-ha!

354
00:30:07,653 --> 00:30:09,848
Oh, I beg your pardon.

355
00:30:10,053 --> 00:30:15,411
Well, this fellow that looked like you
had a friend, a human hippopotamus.

356
00:30:15,613 --> 00:30:18,969
Why, if I had that mass of blubber
here right now...

357
00:30:19,133 --> 00:30:20,805
...I'd crush him alive.

358
00:30:21,253 --> 00:30:23,244
Like this.

359
00:30:23,453 --> 00:30:25,250
[NUTS CRUNCH]

360
00:30:29,933 --> 00:30:35,212
<i>Señores y señoras,</i> now we present
the original Latin bombshell...

361
00:30:35,573 --> 00:30:37,245
...Conchita.

362
00:30:38,893 --> 00:30:40,804
<i>Muchas gracias.</i>

363
00:30:41,093 --> 00:30:43,084
[BAND PLAYS]

364
00:30:43,293 --> 00:30:45,523
[SINGS IN SPANISH]

365
00:33:05,253 --> 00:33:07,608
Marvelous, Conchita, marvelous.

366
00:33:07,773 --> 00:33:10,412
Oh, may I present Don Sebastian.
Señorita Conchita.

367
00:33:10,613 --> 00:33:12,251
<i>- Mucho gusto.</i>
<i>- Sí.</i>

368
00:33:12,453 --> 00:33:14,887
Take a bow. Not a big one.

369
00:33:15,373 --> 00:33:17,807
Oh, <i>mi muchachito,</i> come.

370
00:33:18,013 --> 00:33:20,732
I'm going to teach you
how to do the rhumba.

371
00:33:20,933 --> 00:33:24,448
Some other time. I'm talking business
with Don Sebastian and Hotshot.

372
00:33:24,613 --> 00:33:27,730
Oh, no, no, no.
You come right now, come on.

373
00:33:27,933 --> 00:33:30,686
I'm only gonna to teach you
two steps of conga, okay?

374
00:33:30,933 --> 00:33:34,050
Now, with your left foot,
you will cover three steps to the left...

375
00:33:34,213 --> 00:33:36,852
...and then you kick to the fourth.
Okay, watch.

376
00:33:37,173 --> 00:33:39,403
One, two, three kick.

377
00:33:39,573 --> 00:33:41,450
One, two, three kick.

378
00:33:41,613 --> 00:33:44,730
Oh, it's very simple.
Come on, let's try it now.

379
00:33:44,933 --> 00:33:47,128
One, two, three kick.

380
00:33:47,293 --> 00:33:49,204
One, two, three kick.

381
00:33:49,413 --> 00:33:54,123
Oh, that's wonderful.
Come on, everybody.

382
00:33:55,293 --> 00:33:57,568
Now, the second one.
The second one, you kick.

383
00:33:57,733 --> 00:34:02,523
You walk just about the same, only you
kick a little bit different, like this, watch.

384
00:34:02,733 --> 00:34:07,249
One, two, back, kick.
One, two, back, kick.

385
00:34:07,453 --> 00:34:11,810
All right, come on.
Attaboy.

386
00:34:12,933 --> 00:34:15,652
Now let's try the fourth one.
Goes like this, watch.

387
00:34:15,893 --> 00:34:21,013
One, two, down.
One, two, down.

388
00:34:21,213 --> 00:34:24,603
Oh, you're doing fine.
You're a brave boy.

389
00:34:24,813 --> 00:34:29,443
Now, one, two, down, up.
One, two...

390
00:34:29,653 --> 00:34:31,052
[PANTS RIP]

391
00:34:31,253 --> 00:34:32,891
[AUDIENCE LAUGHS]

392
00:34:34,173 --> 00:34:36,892
There's a strange mule in my stall.
Take that mask off.

393
00:34:37,053 --> 00:34:39,613
Go on, go on, get out of here.

394
00:34:40,413 --> 00:34:42,369
You better go back.

395
00:34:47,813 --> 00:34:49,724
[HARDY YELLS, PLATES CRASH]

396
00:34:59,933 --> 00:35:01,889
Come on, man.

397
00:35:02,133 --> 00:35:04,249
- I'm terribly sorry.
- The pleasure's mutual.

398
00:35:04,413 --> 00:35:06,369
It's all right.

399
00:35:12,253 --> 00:35:13,368
Most embarrassing.

400
00:35:20,413 --> 00:35:22,927
Lucky for me,
I got two pairs of pants with this suit.

401
00:35:23,173 --> 00:35:27,849
- You can't beat Señor Guttenberg.
- A telephone call for you, Don Sebastian.

402
00:35:30,373 --> 00:35:31,567
<i>Sí.</i>

403
00:35:31,773 --> 00:35:33,001
Is this you, Stan?

404
00:35:34,333 --> 00:35:36,130
<i>Sí, señora.</i>

405
00:35:37,053 --> 00:35:39,613
Hello, hello.

406
00:35:44,333 --> 00:35:47,450
- lf he's bullfighter, I'm Mickey Mouse.
- He's a cute little person.

407
00:35:48,133 --> 00:35:50,408
Another call for you.

408
00:35:52,773 --> 00:35:53,762
<i>Sí.</i>

409
00:35:54,253 --> 00:35:57,086
- Who is this?
- This is me. <i>Sí.</i>

410
00:36:00,133 --> 00:36:03,091
Hello, hello.

411
00:36:05,413 --> 00:36:09,167
That reminds me.
I must talk to the committee. Luis.

412
00:36:09,853 --> 00:36:12,447
- Bring me the telephone.
- I'm very sorry, it is busy...

413
00:36:12,653 --> 00:36:14,450
...but you can use the one
in the booth.

414
00:36:14,613 --> 00:36:16,524
- Will you pardon me?
- Careful, your pants.

415
00:36:16,733 --> 00:36:18,610
Oh, thanks.

416
00:36:20,533 --> 00:36:22,603
Thanks for the lovely time,
Mr. Potshot.

417
00:36:22,813 --> 00:36:24,166
Hotshot.

418
00:36:24,373 --> 00:36:27,092
- Well, I've got to be going. You see...
- Where are you going?

419
00:36:27,293 --> 00:36:29,329
- I got to meet Ollie...
- You're going nowhere.

420
00:36:29,493 --> 00:36:32,326
We haven't set this deal yet.
Sit still and enjoy yourself...

421
00:36:32,493 --> 00:36:35,007
...and don't speak English.
<i>- Sí.</i>

422
00:36:35,213 --> 00:36:37,090
Potshot.

423
00:36:38,693 --> 00:36:41,526
I thought you said it was Hotshot.

424
00:36:54,453 --> 00:36:57,923
- Another call for you.
- Hello.

425
00:36:58,293 --> 00:37:00,887
- Hello, Stan, this is Ollie.
- Where are you?

426
00:37:01,093 --> 00:37:02,651
I'm in the telephone booth.

427
00:37:02,853 --> 00:37:07,131
You'd better get out of there. Muldoon's
on his way over to make a call.

428
00:37:09,053 --> 00:37:11,567
Oh! Oh, oh!

429
00:37:13,213 --> 00:37:15,773
Muldoon must have got him.
Come on.

430
00:37:19,413 --> 00:37:21,085
What happened?

431
00:37:21,733 --> 00:37:23,724
Get to the hotel. I'll see you later.

432
00:37:23,933 --> 00:37:25,810
Go on. Beat it.

433
00:37:28,413 --> 00:37:30,290
[PANTS RIP]

434
00:37:34,825 --> 00:37:36,702
- I'll sure be glad to get out of here.
- So will I.

435
00:37:36,905 --> 00:37:39,055
As soon as Mr. Hotfoot
comes with the money...

436
00:37:39,225 --> 00:37:40,499
...we'll be on our way.

437
00:37:40,665 --> 00:37:43,304
His name is not Hotfoot,
it's Hotshot.

438
00:37:43,505 --> 00:37:44,824
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

439
00:37:45,065 --> 00:37:46,657
Come in.

440
00:37:46,865 --> 00:37:49,333
- Well, good morning, gentlemen.
- Good morning.

441
00:37:49,545 --> 00:37:51,342
You're not preparing to leave, are you?

442
00:37:51,545 --> 00:37:53,934
We certainly are.
After that experience last night...

443
00:37:54,145 --> 00:37:56,261
...we don't want to run
into Mr. Muldoon again.

444
00:37:56,465 --> 00:37:59,343
- Why? Nothing happened.
- Yeah, but it was a very close shave.

445
00:37:59,505 --> 00:38:01,860
I have some bad news.
I'm in a terrible spot.

446
00:38:02,025 --> 00:38:05,574
I received a telegram, Don Sebastian's
passport has been held indefinitely...

447
00:38:05,745 --> 00:38:08,054
...and he can't arrive
in time for the big fight.

448
00:38:08,225 --> 00:38:10,341
- So what?
- So what!

449
00:38:10,585 --> 00:38:14,100
I've signed a contract, accepted a check
in advance, you've been advertised.

450
00:38:14,265 --> 00:38:16,221
Last night, you were
seen as Don Sebastian.

451
00:38:16,385 --> 00:38:19,775
So from now on, you are Don Sebastian,
and you have to go through with it.

452
00:38:19,985 --> 00:38:22,180
- You mean you want me to fight a bull?
- Exactly.

453
00:38:22,385 --> 00:38:25,422
- That boy can't fight any bull.
- Listen, there's nothing to it.

454
00:38:25,665 --> 00:38:28,577
I'll get you an old,
contented, blind bull.

455
00:38:28,785 --> 00:38:32,095
Old, blind or contented, I won't do it.

456
00:38:32,305 --> 00:38:34,421
- I don't blame you, Stanley.
- Thank you, Ollie.

457
00:38:34,625 --> 00:38:37,935
- Gentlemen, can I use your telephone?
- Help yourself.

458
00:38:38,145 --> 00:38:39,976
Me fight a blind, contented bull.

459
00:38:40,145 --> 00:38:42,784
Get me Richard K. Muldoon.

460
00:38:45,625 --> 00:38:47,343
Operator.

461
00:38:50,745 --> 00:38:52,178
Oh...

462
00:38:53,105 --> 00:38:54,333
Gump!

463
00:38:54,585 --> 00:38:57,258
- What is it, boss?
- Get Muldoon.

464
00:39:08,025 --> 00:39:09,663
Stanley...

465
00:39:10,505 --> 00:39:14,259
...on second thought,
I think you'd better consider this.

466
00:39:14,465 --> 00:39:15,818
What do you mean consider?

467
00:39:16,025 --> 00:39:19,062
- Don't jump at conclusions.
- Who's jumping?

468
00:39:19,225 --> 00:39:21,739
And don't make hasty decisions.

469
00:39:21,945 --> 00:39:25,733
Don't be so selfish.
Think of me once in a while.

470
00:39:25,945 --> 00:39:28,539
At least you can do this for my sake.

471
00:39:28,745 --> 00:39:30,019
For your sake?

472
00:39:30,185 --> 00:39:33,222
You don't wanna see me skinned alive,
do you?

473
00:39:33,425 --> 00:39:35,222
Listen, you have only one alternative.

474
00:39:35,385 --> 00:39:38,183
Either honor and glory
as thousands cheer...

475
00:39:38,345 --> 00:39:41,382
...or slow death
by my good friend Muldoon.

476
00:39:41,585 --> 00:39:43,257
What do you say?

477
00:39:43,745 --> 00:39:46,259
I don't know, but I think I'm hooked.

478
00:39:46,465 --> 00:39:47,898
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

479
00:39:49,825 --> 00:39:51,816
- Who's there?
MULDOON: Muldoon.

480
00:39:52,025 --> 00:39:53,617
And...

481
00:39:57,145 --> 00:40:01,138
- Well, come in, Richard K.
- Hi, Hotshot. Hello, Sebastian.

482
00:40:09,185 --> 00:40:10,777
Well, now...

483
00:40:10,985 --> 00:40:12,213
I have good news for you.

484
00:40:12,385 --> 00:40:14,421
This week, we have
the finest bulls in years.

485
00:40:14,585 --> 00:40:16,416
- Really?
- Here's the committee selection.

486
00:40:16,585 --> 00:40:18,257
A big, fine, black, courageous one.

487
00:40:18,425 --> 00:40:20,620
No, no, no. This one.

488
00:40:20,825 --> 00:40:25,296
Big fighter, so quick that he turns his
tail around on a <i>peso.</i>

489
00:40:25,505 --> 00:40:28,622
- There's a beautiful animal.
- Fine bull.

490
00:40:28,825 --> 00:40:33,216
- Last Sunday, he killed three matadors.
- Three, mind you.

491
00:40:33,425 --> 00:40:36,417
- What about the blind and contented one?
- Blind and contented?

492
00:40:36,585 --> 00:40:39,019
That's a breed of bulls
they have in Barcelona, Spain.

493
00:40:39,225 --> 00:40:41,455
Leave the pictures
and I'll make our selections.

494
00:40:41,665 --> 00:40:46,944
You can't go wrong. Those bulls are
killer and worthy of your fine technique.

495
00:40:47,145 --> 00:40:49,136
You said it, kid.

496
00:40:49,345 --> 00:40:52,781
Take Don Sebastian out to the bull
farm and let him make his own selection.

497
00:40:52,985 --> 00:40:55,340
- Good idea. I'll call you later.
- Fine, <i>adiós.</i>

498
00:40:55,545 --> 00:40:57,183
<i>- Adiós.</i>
<i>- Adiós.</i>

499
00:40:58,265 --> 00:41:01,416
- Come along, Conchita.
- No, no, no, come on this way.

500
00:41:01,585 --> 00:41:03,735
- I beg your pardon. <i>Adiós.</i>
<i>- Adiós.</i>

501
00:41:06,465 --> 00:41:08,103
Help!

502
00:41:10,425 --> 00:41:13,542
Blind and contented bulls.
I ought to...

503
00:41:17,225 --> 00:41:19,819
Here are Señor Muldoon's finest bulls.

504
00:41:20,025 --> 00:41:23,222
This is my son, Pancho. He's gonna be
a great bullfighter someday.

505
00:41:23,705 --> 00:41:26,424
You hear that? Even the little kid
isn't afraid of the bulls.

506
00:41:26,585 --> 00:41:28,780
- How do you know he's not afraid?
- I'll ask him.

507
00:41:28,985 --> 00:41:31,374
- You aren't afraid of the bulls?
<i>- Sí, señor.</i>

508
00:41:31,665 --> 00:41:32,700
He said, "Yes."

509
00:41:32,865 --> 00:41:35,015
- He said, "Yes," he wasn't, right?
- No, señor.

510
00:41:35,185 --> 00:41:36,664
- You see.
- Here's a fine bull.

511
00:41:36,865 --> 00:41:39,584
He comes from a very fine family.
His name is Little Caesar.

512
00:41:39,785 --> 00:41:41,696
- Little Caesar.
- His brother Big Caesar...

513
00:41:41,905 --> 00:41:44,055
...killed a matador last week.
- Killed?

514
00:41:44,265 --> 00:41:48,941
<i>Sí,</i> one slip of the foot, too slow
in the wrist, it's all over.

515
00:41:49,145 --> 00:41:53,138
- Where is Big Caesar now?
- He's inside, come, I'll show you.

516
00:41:54,185 --> 00:41:55,823
This way, señor.

517
00:42:08,625 --> 00:42:10,855
Now cut that out.

518
00:42:17,305 --> 00:42:18,977
[LAUGHS]

519
00:42:21,185 --> 00:42:23,540
Oh, come on.

520
00:42:35,385 --> 00:42:38,138
You have seen all the bulls
on the farm except these two.

521
00:42:38,345 --> 00:42:40,575
Now you see? There...

522
00:42:41,385 --> 00:42:43,341
Come here.

523
00:42:44,945 --> 00:42:47,937
There's nothing to be afraid of.

524
00:42:48,545 --> 00:42:51,105
This one here, he's <i>loco.</i>
He's a killer.

525
00:42:51,265 --> 00:42:55,178
- Well, how about this one down here?
- He's gentle, he's kind, he's contented.

526
00:42:55,345 --> 00:42:56,778
Are you sure of that?

527
00:42:57,265 --> 00:42:58,664
They call him a gentleman cow.

528
00:42:58,865 --> 00:43:02,062
There you see?
Gentle, kind and contented.

529
00:43:05,545 --> 00:43:07,376
I'm not gonna fight that bull, Ollie.

530
00:43:07,585 --> 00:43:10,895
Listen, you heard what the man said.
They're gentle, kind and contented.

531
00:43:11,105 --> 00:43:15,144
- Why, that bull wouldn't hurt a fly.
- Yeah, but I'm not a fly.

532
00:43:17,145 --> 00:43:18,658
[YELLING]

533
00:43:21,265 --> 00:43:22,459
[SPEAKS SPANISH]

534
00:43:24,905 --> 00:43:27,100
[YELLING]

535
00:44:02,265 --> 00:44:03,698
Stop, come back with my wagon.

536
00:44:09,745 --> 00:44:11,895
Stanley, stop it.

537
00:44:19,345 --> 00:44:21,654
Look out for that tree.

538
00:44:23,425 --> 00:44:25,541
[HARDY GRUNTS AND GROANS]

539
00:44:35,745 --> 00:44:37,815
Come here.

540
00:44:39,625 --> 00:44:42,697
Get that thing off of me
and take it easy.

541
00:44:42,945 --> 00:44:44,981
[GRUNTS AND GROANS]

542
00:45:00,705 --> 00:45:02,900
- Come on.
- Where are you going?

543
00:45:03,105 --> 00:45:07,542
Thanks to you,
I've got to see Señor Guttenberg.

544
00:45:15,105 --> 00:45:17,175
[CROWD CHATTERS INDISTINCTLY]

545
00:45:29,065 --> 00:45:31,579
[TRUMPETS PLAY]

546
00:46:04,865 --> 00:46:06,901
There you are.

547
00:46:08,145 --> 00:46:10,215
I wish we'd never met
that Mr. Shotfoot.

548
00:46:10,385 --> 00:46:11,534
Now, don't worry.

549
00:46:11,705 --> 00:46:14,663
Remember, every cloud
has a silver lining...

550
00:46:14,825 --> 00:46:16,975
...and look at the money
we're gonna get.

551
00:46:17,145 --> 00:46:18,863
- How much?
- Mr. Hotshot gave me...

552
00:46:19,025 --> 00:46:22,017
...his word of honor
that we'd get half of what he gets.

553
00:46:22,185 --> 00:46:25,495
Well, well, well, wonderful.
You look like a million dollars.

554
00:46:25,665 --> 00:46:28,463
You ought to see the greatest crowd
in Mexico City's history.

555
00:46:28,625 --> 00:46:30,741
I wish I had half of that gate.

556
00:46:30,945 --> 00:46:32,697
- Is that all we're going to get?
- What?

557
00:46:32,865 --> 00:46:34,856
A piece of gate.

558
00:46:35,065 --> 00:46:37,533
[MATADOR MOANS]

559
00:46:46,145 --> 00:46:47,544
Probably carelessness.

560
00:46:47,745 --> 00:46:50,498
- I'm not going to do it, I'll tell you.
- Come here, brother.

561
00:46:50,665 --> 00:46:52,144
This is what you need.

562
00:46:52,345 --> 00:46:54,620
Take a shot of this,
it'll give you courage.

563
00:46:54,825 --> 00:46:56,577
There you are.

564
00:47:01,345 --> 00:47:03,540
That settles it.

565
00:47:07,785 --> 00:47:09,377
- Beat it. Here's Muldoon.
- Muldoon.

566
00:47:09,545 --> 00:47:11,263
Muldoon.

567
00:47:15,225 --> 00:47:17,693
- Come in, Richard K.
- Hi, Don Sebastian.

568
00:47:18,025 --> 00:47:21,222
Just dropped in to wish you good luck
and brought a present for you...

569
00:47:21,425 --> 00:47:23,336
...I thought you might like.
This sword...

570
00:47:23,505 --> 00:47:27,054
...belonged to Jose Acapulco,
the greatest <i>toreador</i> in Mexico.

571
00:47:27,265 --> 00:47:31,053
Why, with this sword,
you could almost skin a bull alive.

572
00:47:31,705 --> 00:47:35,300
- Thanks.
- How well I remember Jose Acapulco.

573
00:47:35,465 --> 00:47:37,933
He was graceful like a dancer.

574
00:47:44,785 --> 00:47:48,858
This is the way he makes his kill.

575
00:47:50,985 --> 00:47:53,021
[HARDY YELLS AS CROWD CHEERS]

576
00:47:53,225 --> 00:47:55,056
Listen to that crowd roar.

577
00:47:55,305 --> 00:47:56,863
Let us drink to your success.

578
00:47:57,065 --> 00:48:02,458
Don Sebastian, today you are going
to make bullfighting history.

579
00:48:03,465 --> 00:48:05,057
<i>Salud!</i>

580
00:48:08,345 --> 00:48:09,744
Good luck.

581
00:48:10,345 --> 00:48:12,813
Come, Conchita, Hotshot,
let's get to our seats.

582
00:48:13,025 --> 00:48:15,061
[SPEAKS SPANISH]

583
00:48:16,025 --> 00:48:18,414
Good luck and take it easy.

584
00:48:25,745 --> 00:48:26,894
Put that down.

585
00:48:27,065 --> 00:48:30,137
You can't drink that stuff
when we've got work to do.

586
00:48:30,345 --> 00:48:33,735
- I feel faint.
- Well, I'll get you some smelling salts.

587
00:48:33,945 --> 00:48:36,982
Now, don't faint until I come back.

588
00:48:38,465 --> 00:48:40,342
[CROWD CHEERS]

589
00:49:07,945 --> 00:49:10,618
<i>- Gracias, señor.</i>
<i>- Gracias.</i>

590
00:49:14,305 --> 00:49:16,500
- Who is that guy?
- Why, that's Don Sebastian.

591
00:49:16,665 --> 00:49:19,463
Don Sebastian? You're crazy,
he's in his dressing room.

592
00:49:19,625 --> 00:49:23,015
Oh, you're crazy,
I just picked him up at the airport.

593
00:49:49,025 --> 00:49:51,141
[MATADOR MOANS]

594
00:49:55,945 --> 00:49:58,334
Skin him alive.

595
00:50:17,865 --> 00:50:21,221
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

596
00:50:42,145 --> 00:50:44,784
I come to wish you luck.

597
00:51:14,505 --> 00:51:15,779
Put that down.

598
00:51:15,985 --> 00:51:17,623
[SPEAKS SPANISH]

599
00:51:17,785 --> 00:51:20,345
See what that stuff is doing?
You're double talking.

600
00:51:20,505 --> 00:51:22,575
Come on, the crowd's waiting.

601
00:51:22,785 --> 00:51:25,618
[SPEAKS SPANISH]

602
00:51:40,985 --> 00:51:44,057
Now, get out there and stay out
of the way of the bull.

603
00:51:44,745 --> 00:51:46,224
[CHEERING]

604
00:51:47,985 --> 00:51:49,976
[TRUMPETS PLAY]

605
00:53:33,625 --> 00:53:34,944
Ooo!

606
00:53:48,865 --> 00:53:51,220
This guy's terrific.
Let me congratulate you.

607
00:53:51,425 --> 00:53:52,778
Knew you'd like him.

608
00:54:13,665 --> 00:54:16,179
- Say, Ollie.
- What?

609
00:54:16,785 --> 00:54:18,537
- You know what?
- What?

610
00:54:18,745 --> 00:54:21,339
I've decided that I'm not gonna fight
any bull.

611
00:54:21,505 --> 00:54:24,383
Get back in that ring.

612
00:54:28,385 --> 00:54:30,899
Now go ahead out there
and fight that bull.

613
00:54:31,105 --> 00:54:32,697
Go on.

614
00:54:56,065 --> 00:54:57,817
- What are you trying to give me?
- What?

615
00:54:58,025 --> 00:55:00,255
- That's Hardy, the flatfoot from Peoria.
- Oh, no.

616
00:55:00,425 --> 00:55:02,893
The other guy is Laurel.
They sent me up for 20 years.

617
00:55:03,065 --> 00:55:06,296
- Now, Richard K, control yourself.
- Control myself, you...

618
00:55:08,425 --> 00:55:11,735
- Turn the bulls loose.
- Turn the bulls loose.

619
00:55:12,065 --> 00:55:15,216
[INDISTINCT CHATTER AND YELLING]

620
00:55:27,225 --> 00:55:28,738
[CRIES]

621
00:55:34,185 --> 00:55:37,780
Hey, Stan, come on,
let's get out of here.

622
00:55:38,705 --> 00:55:40,855
Come on, Stan, I think...

623
00:56:44,705 --> 00:56:48,141
Hey, Stan, let's get out of here,
Muldoon.

624
00:56:57,945 --> 00:57:00,334
Pardon me, señoritas.

625
00:57:06,145 --> 00:57:08,784
Sure was clever the way you
gave Muldoon the slip.

626
00:57:08,945 --> 00:57:12,494
Thank you, Stanley. Now always
remember any time you get in trouble...

627
00:57:12,665 --> 00:57:15,179
...you can depend upon me.
- Thank you, Ollie.

628
00:57:15,345 --> 00:57:17,859
Get our overcoats
and we'll sneak down the fire escape.

629
00:57:18,025 --> 00:57:19,663
Now there's another clever idea.

630
00:57:19,865 --> 00:57:23,301
- He'll never expect us to go that way.
- No.

631
00:57:23,505 --> 00:57:26,622
You sure are full of ideas, Ollie.

632
00:57:41,785 --> 00:57:43,776
First, the little one...

633
00:57:43,985 --> 00:57:46,215
...then the big one.

634
00:57:49,345 --> 00:57:51,939
Take your clothes off.

635
00:57:56,105 --> 00:57:58,858
- Thank you, Ollie.
- You're welcome.

636
00:58:01,745 --> 00:58:04,179
Oh, don't get that dirty.

637
00:58:04,385 --> 00:58:07,377
Well, here's another nice mess
you've gotten me into.

638
00:58:07,585 --> 00:58:09,098
Well, I couldn't help it.

639
00:58:09,305 --> 00:58:13,184
Come on, let's get back
to Peoria where we belong.

640
00:58:13,385 --> 00:58:15,376
[BONES CLATTER]

